<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by gunner91980 on 04-19-2001 05:57 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Another aspect of the camping problems is vendors. I mean think about it. What items do u buy from vendors to equip after lvl 1-10??? After that full set of leather and bastard sword gets replaced there's no more use for vendors as equipable-item sellers. I mean just look at the price versus AC of chain and plate armor. I can get an entire set of banded for about 1/15th the price of a set of chain armor from a vendor and it's got far more ac. 1500pp for a plate mail breastplate with 17ac???? You would need to be lvl 35+ minimum to reasonably afford that without cheating and by then what good is a meager 17ac BP? I've never seen any weapon worth buying from vendors past level 10. I don't know about all of you but one of the things I liked best about RPG's was being able to travel to a new town and see what kindof good wpns + armor i could get there. In EQ that does not exsist. Also, why does that vendor buy my gnoll hide lariat for 1pp and then sell it for 25pp??? I always thought that vendors should buy for about half what they sell for. (Ex.) I loot a chain-mail skirt from a MOB in South Karana. This item sells in the store for about 100-200pp they offer 3pp for it... What is up with that??? My runewood great staff is worth 1Kpp, vendor will buy for 5pp. There isn't a higher lvl player anywhere thats going to make that sale. Verant has managed to make even the simple act of selling loot an excruciatingly long process to get anywhere near a reasonable price. Frankly, I dont feel like sitting in East Commons tunnel auctioning for 6+ hours (real-time) just to sell any decent items ive looted. I know that there is no chance of VI putting decent equip for sale on vendors. So why can't they at least put armor or weapons I would equip on the same level mobs? Or at least on quests that can be completed at the same level. As far as I know the only way to get somewhat decent equip is to save a ton of money and get it from player auctions. If higher level people weren't camping items it wouldn't be surprising to see lvl 25+ players still running around in banded/bronze. </TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
